canonical:
  title: 后土祝
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 騰精于天躔六星而垂象受祀于地位五土以配神爰選震辰敢修菲奠覬枉密扶之力奄觀多稔之年
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 后土祝
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 騰精于天。躔六星而垂象。受祀于地。位五土以配神。爰選震辰。敢修菲奠。覬枉密扶之力。奄觀多稔之年。
korean:
  title: 토지신 축문
  author: 김극기
  language: kor
  text: 정기(精氣)가 하늘에 오르매, 육성(六星)을 운행하여 조짐을 드러내 보이고 땅에서 제사를 받으매, 오방(五方)의 토지에 각기 맡은 신(神)을 배치하였습니다. 이제 좋은 때를 가리어서 감히 간략한 제전(祭典)을 드리며, 보이지 않는 곳에서 굽어 붙들어 주시는 힘을 바라오니, 문득 풍년이 드는 것을 보게 하소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1130_020_0020&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Invocation to the Earth Deity
  author: Kim Geuk-gi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Essence and spirit ascend to heaven,
    Traversing the six stars to reveal their portents;
    Blessings descend upon the earth,
    Where the five directions each hold their appointed spirit.

    Now in this auspicious season, we dare to offer
    This humble sacrifice and modest rite.
    We beseech your invisible hand,
    Your gentle strength that upholds all things,
    That we might witness the harvest's abundance
    And see the fields bow heavy with plenty.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'six stars' likely refers to celestial configurations used in East Asian astronomical divination practices.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'five directions' (including center) correspond to the five phases and their associated earthly domains in classical Chinese cosmology.
  - key: ''
    value: This invocation is structured as a formal petition combining celestial observation with earthly gratitude, typical of agricultural prayers in East Asian tradition.
